Elytra oblong, widest at middle, striae moderately impressed, with fine and dense punctures, intervals weakly convex, with fine, dense punctures and fine setae, some spots glabrous and smooth, with only single coarse punctures each bearing a long erect seta (partly abraded in 
holotype
); epipleural edge very fine, ending well before strongly rounded external apical angle of elytra, epipleura densely setose, apical border chitinous, without short microtrichomes.
